# Git Commits

## No Cursor co-author

Never include `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>` (or any Cursor co-author trailer) in commit messages. Commits must show only the user's authorship on GitHub.

## How to commit safely

Cursor may auto-inject the co-author line via `git commit`. When committing in this repo:

1. Write the message to a temp file (no co-author lines).
2. Create the commit with direct Git, bypassing injection:

```powershell
$tree = (git rev-parse "HEAD^{tree}").Trim()
# For new commits on top of HEAD, use normal parent; for amend of tip, use HEAD^ or commit-tree with -p
& "C:\Program Files\Git\mingw64\bin\git.exe" commit-tree $tree -p (git rev-parse HEAD^) -F path/to/msg.txt
```

For a **new commit** (not rewriting history), prefer:

```powershell
git add <files>
& "C:\Program Files\Git\mingw64\bin\git.exe" commit -F path/to/msg.txt --no-verify
```

If the message still contains `Co-authored-by: Cursor`, rewrite with `git.exe commit-tree` and `git reset --hard <new-sha>` before pushing.

## Before push

Verify the message is clean:

```powershell
git log -1 --format=%B
```

Reject and fix any commit that still contains `Co-authored-by: Cursor`.

## Push policy

- Do not push unless the user asks.
- Do not force-push to `main` unless the user explicitly requests fixing commit metadata (e.g. removing co-author).
